Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.63,0:01:54.03,Default,,0,0,0,,An unexpected reunion with Lotte helped Luise \Novercome a crisis, through changing places with Lotte again.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.87,0:02:03.51,Default,,0,0,0,,But immediately after that, both - Lotte with mother \Nand Luise with father - retired in the different directions. {/went to live together}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.04,0:02:07.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte and Luise will remember \Nthis fleeting moment of happiness. {/submerged in ...}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.94,0:02:10.11,Default,,0,0,0,,But what's coming to the two now? {really no clue what's implied under the ellipsis here, doesn't seem to be the continuation of previous line either}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.91,0:02:15.92,Sign,,0,0,100,,{\c&HEAFCF9&\bord0\blur0.8\fs20}Episode 16 \N {\fs35} Quirk of Fate {運命のいたずら} \N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N {\fs23} \h Translation: Perevodildo | Timings: Sub-RoRo \h
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.09,0:02:27.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Long time no see, Munich breakfast.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.92,0:02:29.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Long time no see, our flat.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.97,0:02:33.21,Default,,0,0,0,,And of course...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.27,0:02:37.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Long time no see, mom!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.01,0:02:42.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Which reminds me, mom last night...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.83,0:02:55.73,Default,,0,0,0,,She seemed oh so happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.96,0:02:58.56,Default,,0,0,0,,With a radiant smile.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.33,0:03:00.93,Default,,0,0,0,,The prettiest of moms!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.47,0:03:08.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Mom and Editor Bernau seem to be advancing \Ntowards each other by leaps and bounds... {fast approach; quick intimacy - not sure what she means}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.05,0:03:14.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.67,0:03:16.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Something happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.78,0:03:21.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I was just thinking about how mom \Nwas even prettier than usual, last night.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.48,0:03:22.35,Default,,0,0,0,,True?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.35,0:03:23.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, true.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.72,0:03:24.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow, glad to hear.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.78,0:03:28.52,Default,,0,0,0,,In that case, maybe I should try finding my love, \Nto start a spring in someone else's soul, too? {no clue what she means: again/another/yet to flourish briefly (esp. before retiring or stopping); to have a day in the limelight; to have a stint of success - would assume "I'm blooming now, so I'll let someone else bloom too"}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.59,0:03:32.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I lied!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.69,0:03:34.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't scare me like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.44,0:03:43.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Your dad made me realize, \NI had my share of men in this life. {lit: men, with your dad alone, fed up}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.68,0:03:52.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Was he really that wicked a person, my dad?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.59,0:03:56.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Well I may be exaggerating it a bit, \Nsaying I had my share. {unsure: saying ... is a joke, but}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.36,0:04:02.43,Default,,0,0,0,,There are wholesome marriages, sure, \Nbut even those seldom coincide with happy marriages. {/...are rare}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.96,0:04:07.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I will never in my life \Nneed anyone else as long as I have Lotte. {/just having lotte is enough}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.93,0:04:11.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah... By Jove, it's so late!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.70,0:04:13.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte, you also gotta hurry! {/finish your preparations}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.30,0:04:14.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah... Wait. Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.77,0:04:20.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte, hurry up!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.38,0:04:21.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Give me a moment!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.67,0:04:25.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah... This Luise! My desk is a jumble because of her!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.85,0:04:27.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Where might the arithmetic textbook be?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.15,0:04:34.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, right, right.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.25,0:04:36.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll be home late today. \NGo ahead and dine without me.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.81,0:04:38.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay. Work?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.51,0:04:42.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. With Editor-in-chief, \Nwe're putting together a report about the concert. {/I have to go collect data}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.47,0:04:54.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Frau Annie, if we don't come in now, \Nthe classes would start without us!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.90,0:04:57.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I said we're waiting until Lotte comes!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.17,0:04:59.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Today, I'm definitely telling her what I think!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.24,0:05:03.61,Default,,0,0,0,,We're not letting her put on airs, \Njust 'cause she can play some lousy piano!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.95,0:05:10.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Also, I need to figure out, \Nhow do I make contact with Luise now?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.73,0:05:12.66,Default,,0,0,0,,The phone is out of question, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.16,0:05:21.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.33,0:05:23.07,Default,,0,0,0,,What was that? \NPicking a fight again?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.07,0:05:27.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I bumped into you because I wasn't paying attention. \NI'm sorry, Annie.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.35,0:05:30.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Exactly! You're the one at fault here!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.78,0:05:36.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Look at you - barely learned some piano, \Nbut thinking you're the cream of the crop already! {just cause you're a little good at piano doesnt mean you're great or anthing}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.52,0:05:38.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I am truly sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.19,0:05:39.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Pay attention next time!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.67,0:05:40.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Pay attention!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.66,0:05:41.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Right, right.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.96,0:05:50.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I can swear they expected me to start a brawl just now. \NEven Annie looked scared at the sight of me!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.49,0:05:55.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I swear, Luise, what kind of monster \Nhave you been molding out of me?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.87,0:06:03.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Miss Körner.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.24,0:06:04.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.08,0:06:08.38,Default,,0,0,0,,For tonight's event, I got us three tickets just in case. \NFeel free to bring Lotte along.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.94,0:06:10.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, Lotte?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.88,0:06:16.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Personally, Palfy's alleged impeccability in arts \Nrubs me the wrong way. {unsure, lit: palfy's arts supremacism side not starting to love - I hope he means "they say that of palfy is supreme art and I don't like such statements"}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.13,0:06:20.10,Default,,0,0,0,,But well, there would also be Prosofsky, \Nsaid to be number one pianist in the world,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.10,0:06:22.70,Default,,0,0,0,,so Lotte might be interested in listening to it, too. {/I thought it's better that ...}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.63,0:06:25.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, thank you then.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.20,0:06:38.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I see, I might bring Lotte along for his concert.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.07,0:06:43.38,Default,,0,0,0,,This can actually do her good - \Nwatching her dad work, even if she doesn't know it's him. {lit: I can show her the shape/appearance of dad's work - I think here she refers to the process of working and not result}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.91,0:06:51.82,Sign,,0,0,0,,Munich Hotel
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.02,0:07:02.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte should soon be back from school, I think.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.47,0:07:06.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Somehow, I'm sure she'll try to call me then. {unsure what she means, Lit is "I feel that she's going to call me" but that'd be obviously stupid thing to expect, especially when it's much easier for you call her yourself}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.06,0:07:13.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Luise, are you ready to go out yet? {"finished preparations" - fuck knows what he means since she is obviously doing nothing, but they all seem to use this very liberally in general sense of "can we proceed to the next step/have you done what you said you'll do"}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.58,0:07:16.25,Default,,0,0,0,,No, not yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.25,0:07:18.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, you'd better hurry.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.08,0:07:22.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll need you to meet Herr Prosofsky,\Nwhom I'm also introducing to musicians today. {orchestra member; musician}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.62,0:07:23.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Who is that man?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.72,0:07:25.89,Default,,0,0,0,,The number one pianist in the world!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.56,0:07:29.67,Default,,0,0,0,,At tonight's concert, he is making a guest appearance. {appearance (in a film, play, TV show, etc.); performance}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.00,0:07:35.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I deemed it necessary to let him listen to your piano.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.98,0:07:43.30,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you think? Awed, aren't you? \NAfter all, good ideas are my trademark, yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.30,0:07:44.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait, though...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.61,0:07:47.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Might as well go ahead\Nand ask him to take you as an apprentice.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.48,0:07:48.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Exactly! That's what we do.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.61,0:07:51.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh my, you gotta be kidding!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.92,0:07:54.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.69,0:07:58.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.13,0:08:01.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, this is me, Ludwig.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.43,0:08:04.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, Frau Irene.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.83,0:08:07.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, what is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.60,0:08:10.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Inviting me and Luise to your place?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.67,0:08:13.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh? A home party?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.75,0:08:15.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, I like it!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.70,0:08:17.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Luise is also delighted.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.81,0:08:20.61,Default,,0,0,0,,He's talking to Frau Irene.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.14,0:08:24.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte's observations were right, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.52,0:08:27.47,Default,,0,0,0,,And dad is also willingly playing courteous with her. {unsure: not all bad; not as dissatisfied (or annoyed) as one would have others believe; not completely displeasing; fairly pleasing​}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.47,0:08:29.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, we'll be looking forward to it!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.35,0:08:31.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, I'll see you when we're back.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.16,0:08:32.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.59,0:08:34.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Good bye.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.39,0:08:41.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Dad.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.53,0:08:43.93,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it, Luise?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.54,0:08:45.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Say,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.50,0:08:48.34,Default,,0,0,0,,the person that just called...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.35,0:08:51.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, you mean Frau Irene?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.79,0:08:53.44,Default,,0,0,0,,You know her too, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.29,0:08:58.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you love her? {/your mistress/lover}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.42,0:09:01.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Could it be, you're marrying her?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.07,0:09:08.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, how do I put it...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.15,0:09:16.24,Default,,0,0,0,,For your dad, life consists of loving things.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.21,0:09:23.35,Default,,0,0,0,,An imposing city street, or beautiful flowers, \Nthen, there are also mountains, seas and even skies. {townscape; street (of stores and houses); (look of) stores and houses on street}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.13,0:09:27.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Without a doubt, pretty women are among those, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.83,0:09:33.10,Default,,0,0,0,,In the world such as ours, all the art is born \Nfrom either loving someone, or being loved.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.89,0:09:37.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Surely, when you grow up, \Nyou'll also give your love to great many things.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.06,0:09:39.43,Default,,0,0,0,,That's not what I meant!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.20,0:09:42.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, you were asking about the marriage?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.70,0:09:45.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Alas, I've had my share of marriage.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.66,0:09:47.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Had your share?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.83,0:09:53.70,Default,,0,0,0,,At the very least, for the moment, \NI don't need anyone else's love, as long as I have my Luise. {/as a loving partner, louise alone suffices}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.70,0:09:57.67,Default,,0,0,0,,But well, I guess I'll have to reconsider, \Nonce you find someone you love yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.40,0:10:02.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll answer it!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.97,0:10:05.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, this is Luise Palfy.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.76,0:10:07.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! Luise, it's me!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.62,0:10:09.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Lo—
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.46,0:10:15.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I'm so glad! \NI was afraid you won't be able to answer. {/I finally contacted you}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.96,0:10:17.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.97,0:10:21.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Mom!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.46,0:10:22.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Mom?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.51,0:10:27.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, wrong number! \NThey just apologized.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.61,0:10:31.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Mom? You said you'd be late today.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.60,0:10:34.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I came to pick you up.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.15,0:10:35.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Pick me up?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.44,0:10:40.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Turns out, when buying tickets for tonight's concert, \Nour Editor-in-chief also took you in account.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.55,0:10:42.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Tonight's concert?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.77,0:10:45.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Big concert of the Munich Symphony Orchestra.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.52,0:10:51.76,Default,,0,0,0,,The guest tonight is the world's number one pianist, \Nso it would only be beneficial for you to listen to.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.79,0:10:55.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, the taxi is waiting for us. Presto, presto!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.00,0:10:57.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.59,0:11:28.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Mom is going to attend dad's concert...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.86,0:11:30.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And she brings me along.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.06,0:11:33.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder, in what feelings mom is going there?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.21,0:11:36.51,Default,,0,0,0,,What feelings?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.87,0:11:43.92,Default,,0,0,0,,A majestic sunset.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.48,0:11:50.42,Default,,0,0,0,,The sunset. It's absolutely majestic.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.16,0:11:58.29,Default,,0,0,0,,You're right!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.95,0:12:24.09,Default,,0,0,0,,After that, I never had a chance to call Lotte again.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.18,0:12:30.80,Default,,0,0,0,,We finally meet after such a long time, \Nand yet we've not even a moment to sit down and talk. {/can't talk leisurely}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.10,0:12:35.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.24,0:12:39.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Luise, the car is here to pick us up.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.18,0:12:40.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.12,0:12:52.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, Herr Chauffeur.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.98,0:12:55.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Could you make a short stop \Nat the gates of that hotel? {/in front of us}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.06,0:13:05.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! That's the hotel where dad is staying!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.80,0:13:08.23,Default,,0,0,0,,What for, mom?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.23,0:13:12.76,Default,,0,0,0,,A critic from France had arrived, \Nso I need to hand him over the manuscript originals. {not sure what she means, lit: Primary source​/materials; data; document of the manuscript; copy; draft; notes; contribution}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.98,0:13:21.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I hope it all goes well. \NLuise might come out at any moment!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.01,0:13:27.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Luise, sure you didn't forget nothing?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.78,0:13:31.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait! The score, the score!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.36,0:13:36.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.21,0:13:51.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Excuse me, I am Körner \Nfrom the Munich Graph magazine.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.59,0:14:03.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't help wondering, \Nwhat may Lotte be up to now?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.24,0:14:24.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Luise! Need to hide! {taihen?}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.44,0:14:28.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte and mom... here, of all places! {/why are they here}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.92,0:14:35.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Take care.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.30,0:15:08.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.84,0:15:10.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Forgot something, after all!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.59,0:15:12.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Really? Even as I told you to make sure! {careless; thoughtless; hasty; rash}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.74,0:15:16.09,Default,,0,0,0,,My bad. I'll go get it in a moment. \NYou just wait for me in the car.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.63,0:15:23.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks a lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.53,0:15:27.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, Lotte, I'll be back in a minute. \NWait here for me, will you?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.64,0:15:29.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. Take your time.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.32,0:15:51.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Let me help you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.12,0:15:51.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Lot—
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.68,0:16:17.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, hey, don't you think, \Nmom might have a thing for Editor Bernau?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.46,0:16:23.46,Default,,0,0,0,,And our Editor also \Nseems to be rather fond of mom.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.76,0:16:28.77,Default,,0,0,0,,They say, women that are in love \Ncan even become prettier, without realizing it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.77,0:16:32.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And mom last night looked the most radiant! {/were shining/dazzling}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.10,0:16:35.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, maybe it was \Nbecause she knew dad is in Munich, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.47,0:16:38.51,Default,,0,0,0,,That would have been fine by me.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.13,0:16:41.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Think they're considering a marriage?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.13,0:16:42.66,Default,,0,0,0,,This doesn't seem likely.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.66,0:16:45.23,Default,,0,0,0,,After all, she said she had her share of marriage.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.23,0:16:45.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.43,0:16:48.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Dad put it in those exact words, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.49,0:16:50.26,Default,,0,0,0,,So there's no hope at all... {/despair}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.59,0:16:55.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Since both are so resentful \Nof their previous marriage experience. {lit: for both, marriage life was such a disastrous; tragic; miserable; wretched; pitiful; woeful}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.09,0:16:59.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Artists are whimsical beings. {/selfish/capricious}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.82,0:17:04.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Refusing to put up with it, \Nmom went on to pursue her own way of life. {lit: A mother who couldn't keep up with it and tried to live her own way of life.}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.23,0:17:07.16,Default,,0,0,0,,There's more to it than meets the eye. {/this is more complicated than you think}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.16,0:17:10.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Life is not making it easy for us... {/difficult problem}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.77,0:17:21.69,Default,,0,0,0,,But at least, dad said, \Nhe doesn't need anyone else's love, as long he has me. {/to love anyone else}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.69,0:17:23.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Mom said it, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.82,0:17:26.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Just loving me is more than enough for her. {As long as she has me, she'll never need anyone else.}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.36,0:17:31.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, at least we know, that for the moment, \Nthey both don't have a special someone.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.03,0:17:32.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.13,0:17:34.00,Default,,0,0,0,,At any rate, both for mom...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.00,0:17:37.77,Default,,0,0,0,,And for dad, we need to keep an eager eye \Nso that they don't end up on a slippery slope.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.24,0:17:38.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.50,0:17:43.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Until we know for sure \Nhow dad and mom actually feel about it...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.00,0:17:48.95,Default,,0,0,0,,...The fact we two ever met \Nshould be kept a secret at any cost.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.38,0:17:52.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Do your best.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.08,0:17:56.55,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll do our best together.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.82,0:18:02.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! Mom!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.89,0:18:07.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I'll go with mom then.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.42,0:18:11.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Luise, no! I'm the one going with mom now!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.34,0:18:12.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, right.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.70,0:18:14.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll call you again tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.00,0:18:19.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Mom!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.10,0:18:20.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, sorry I made you wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.84,0:18:22.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, shall we go?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.85,0:18:34.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Now that I think of it, \Nwhere might Lotte be heading to now?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.39,0:18:45.83,Default,,0,0,0,,My, we'll be late, Luise.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.83,0:18:47.96,Default,,0,0,0,,What's taking you so long?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.69,0:19:12.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Look, Editor. The interviews we need to take \Nare with Herr Prosofsky and with Palfy.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.32,0:19:14.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, about that... \NI wonder if that'll be enough. {yokatta no kashira?}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.66,0:19:20.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Still, I'd never think I'll get to attend \Ndad's concert, looking like this. {method; manner; way; style}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.60,0:19:21.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.94,0:19:24.41,Default,,0,0,0,,What are the chances Luise is also around?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.48,0:19:29.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, and we could include a photo in this one.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.07,0:19:31.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, the other photos...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.64,0:19:38.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, I hope for some good answers, \Nbut just getting them to speak would be a feat already.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.96,0:19:39.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Right, right.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.97,0:19:43.22,Default,,0,0,0,,But that's exactly the kind of thing \Nyou've acquired such a knack for. {But isn't it your skill to make it work?}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.22,0:19:45.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm pinning my hopes on you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.89,0:19:50.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Even thought I know \Nthey're merely talking about the work...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.76,0:19:56.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, I guess, I'll go take my seat \Nin the auditorium now. {/will go to the audience}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.00,0:19:59.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. Your seat would be \Nthe third in the A section on the second floor. {unsure about A section part, maybe there's a better word in english}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.61,0:20:02.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't let Herr Prometheus overshadow you. {i hope she means this by "don't lose to"}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.11,0:20:06.84,Default,,0,0,0,,It's "Prosofsky."
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.35,0:20:09.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I'll be trying my utmost either way!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.52,0:20:13.29,Default,,0,0,0,,See you!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.12,0:20:18.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, when it's over, \Nwe'll go get something delicious to eat. {/somewhere}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.23,0:20:20.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.31,0:20:43.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Section A, seat three...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.79,0:20:46.29,Default,,0,0,0,,There! Found it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.66,0:21:00.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.16,0:21:03.33,Default,,0,0,0,,How come you all are also here?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.64,0:21:06.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Luise...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.24,0:21:09.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't tell me this is your seat...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.20,0:21:35.77,Default,,0,0,0,,What else do you call this, \Nif not an ironic quirk of fate? {/mischieveous}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.77,0:21:39.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Four people - the entire family \Nended up together in a place like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.63,0:21:42.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Will they prevent this \Nfrom escalating into a kerfuffle? {lit: There is no way it won't cause a ruckus/disturbance; kerfuffle - not sure what he means}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.67,0:21:49.14,Default,,0,0,0,,With bated breath, I pray that Lotte and Luise \Nare spared the woeful fate. {lit: I pray; I wish that misfortune never come to Lotte and Luise}
Comment: 0,0:22:03.07,0:22:03.07,Sign,,0,0,0,,{chapter}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.01,0:22:12.54,Sign,,0,0,0,,A miserable romance {可哀想ね　ロマンス}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.54,0:22:16.00,Sign,,0,0,0,,A tear-jerking nuance {涙誘うニュアンス}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.00,0:22:19.72,Sign,,0,0,0,,If you turn another page of your memories, {想い出のページめくれば}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.72,0:22:22.63,Sign,,0,0,0,,Here she is - heroine of the past {追憶のヒロイン} {actually, "the heroine of the recollections" but that doesn't have a nice ring to it}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.85,0:22:34.27,Sign,,0,0,0,,I raise my eyes to your face - {あなたの面影　見上げて咲いている}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.27,0:22:38.03,Sign,,0,0,0,,Suddenly, I'm in full bloom {unsure, maybe "it's flourishing"}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.03,0:22:41.57,Sign,,0,0,0,,A sunflower amidst the blizzard - {act. in the middle of winter}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.57,0:22:44.97,Sign,,0,0,0,,that would be me, my dear {真冬のひまわり　それが私なの}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.41,0:22:48.14,Sign,,0,0,0,,Always on the verge of freezing, {凍えるような気持ちでいつも}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.99,0:22:51.54,Sign,,0,0,0,,My feelings are out of control -
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.54,0:22:56.09,Sign,,0,0,0,,Too stiff to even say "Do you still love me?" {「好き?」と尋くこともできず}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.09,0:23:00.24,Sign,,0,0,0,,My lips just keep wavering in this wind! {風に揺れていたわ}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.79,0:23:05.44,Sign,,0,0,0,,A pitiful Romance {いじらしいね　ロマンス}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.44,0:23:08.85,Sign,,0,0,0,,Something that only happens in dreams: {夢のような出来事}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.85,0:23:12.48,Sign,,0,0,0,,Trying hard to forget, I fell even more in love {忘れるために愛したの}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.48,0:23:15.25,Sign,,0,0,0,,with heroine of the past {追憶のヒロイン}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.30,0:23:20.07,Sign,,0,0,0,,Miracle that I came across now is hugging me tight {めぐりあえた奇跡　そっと抱きしめて}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.07,0:23:23.48,Sign,,0,0,0,,This is the story of my life, I'll do my best to protect it! {私だけの歴史　守ってゆくわ}
Comment: 0,0:23:27.07,0:23:27.07,Sign,,0,0,0,,{chapter}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.74,0:23:29.28,Sign,,0,0,0,,Next episode
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.12,0:23:33.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Lotte, something really bad happened!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.62,0:23:34.36,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.36,0:23:37.69,Default,,0,0,0,,We happened to be sitting \Nnext to each other on the concert!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.69,0:23:38.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh? No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.56,0:23:41.83,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a disaster! After all, \Nmom and Editor-in-chief are also here!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.83,0:23:43.40,Default,,0,0,0,,But there's more. There's more to it!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.40,0:23:46.59,Default,,0,0,0,,The worst thing of all - \NAnnie is sitting to the other side of me!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.59,0:23:48.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh no! What do we do, Luise?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.59,0:23:50.03,Default,,0,0,0,,We're screwed!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.03,0:23:51.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Totally done for! {end of life; death; breathing one's last}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.20,0:23:53.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Next time in I and Myself:
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.97,0:23:55.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Munich in an Uproar!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.30,0:23:57.50,Sign,,0,0,0,,Episode 17 \NMunich in an Uproar!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.43,0:23:56.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't miss it!
